### Architecture Constraints

1. **Agent-initiated** — The LLM decides when to revert, not the orchestrator
2. **Scoped to current run** — Agent can only revert files within its own run
3. **Two revert targets** — "task_start" (undo my changes) or "run_start" (reset to clean state)
4. **Selective revert** — Agent can revert a single file or all managed files
5. **Consistent across agent types** — Same tool semantics for MCP, OpenHands, and CLI

